NAME
       gfloppy - a simple floppy formatter for the GNOME

SYNOPSIS
       gfloppy

       or  select  gfloppy from the Utilities submenu of the Main
       Menu.

       or right click on the floppy  icon  on  your  desktop  and
       select Format Floppy

DESCRIPTION
       GFloppy  is  a simple floppy formatter for Linux.  It sup­
       ports the DOS format and the ext2 file system.   In  order
       to create DOS floppies you need to have the mtools package
       installed.

       For full documentation see the GFloppy online help.

OPTIONS
       In addition to the standard GNOME options GFloppy supports
       the following one.

       --device=DEVICE
              The device to format (instead of /dev/fd0).

